FBIS3-52638 "drnes004_p_94005" FBIS-NES-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Hekmatyar Would Welcome Pakistan as Mediator BK0501155594 Hong Kong AFP in English 1541 GMT 5 Jan 94 BK0501155594 Hong Kong AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Islamabad, Jan 5 (AFP) -- Afghan Prime Minister Golboddin Hekmatyar would welcome any visit from Pakistan aimed at restoring peace in Kabul, his official representative here said Wednesday. "Hekmatyar has always welcomed visitors from Pakistan," Mangal Hoseyn said in a statement on the Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of Afghanistan] leader's response to a planned mediation trip to Kabul by Pakistani Foreign Minister Asif Ahmad Ali. The foreign minister had to put off a scheduled visit after fighting broke out in Kabul on New Year's Day. "We respect Pakistan's concern for peace and stability in Afghanistan and are always ready to receive any delegation from the brotherly country," Hoseyn said.
